9%85%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AF%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be glorious, to be exalted"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to praise, to glorify"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَجَدَ (majada, “to be glorious”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"magnificence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nobility, honor"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare مَجِيد (majīd, “glorious”). Cognate with Hebrew מגד.\n\nCausative of مَجَدَ (majada, “to be glorious”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5182","headword_ar":"مُجِدٌّ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAd~N","text_ar":"جَادٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA lmjd~p biAlr~ajuli","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لمجدّة بِالرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase mentioned by As, said of a she-camel, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily she is quick in her pace with the man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says, I know not whether he said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mijad~apN","text_ar":"مِجَدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujid~apN","text_ar":"مُجِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former would be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the latter, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~a","text_ar":"اَجَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38222","headword_ar":"مَجَدَ","root":"mjd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majuda","text_ar":"مَجُدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majaAdapN","text_ar":"مَجَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, possessed of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"characterized by,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majod","text_ar":"مَجْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glory, honour, dignity, nobility, &c.; he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, glorious, in a state of honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity, noble, &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below]. (S, L, K.) ―         -b2-  See 3. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majadati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"مَجَدَتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, IAar, S, L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujuwdN","text_ar":"مُجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, S, L, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amjdt","text_ar":"امجدت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels fed in a land abounding with pasturage, and satiated themselves therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, L:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lighted upon abundant pasturage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, L, K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obtained of fresh herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalFY","text_ar":"خَلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearly as much as satiated them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and their bodies made this known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) See 4. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majadati Alganamu","text_ar":"مَجَدَتِ الغَنَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujuwdN","text_ar":"مُجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, ate of leguminous plants so as to blunt the sharpness of their hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-  [Hence, app., accord. to the A, the signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majada","text_ar":"مَجَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majuda","text_ar":"مَجُدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"given in the commencement of this art.]"}],"source_refs":["AZ","IAar","S","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n38228","headword_ar":"مَجْدٌ","root":"mjd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Glory; honour; dignity; nobility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafN","text_ar":"شَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] (L, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karamN","text_ar":"كَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquisition of glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayolu $arafK","text_ar":"نَيْلُ شَرَفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, L, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquisition of what suffices thereof and of lordship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) [and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquired glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, transmitted by one's ancestors:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) ISk says, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majod","text_ar":"مَجْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araf","text_ar":"شَرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"are [transmitted] by one's ancestors; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasab","text_ar":"حَسَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karam","text_ar":"كَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"may belong to a man without ancestors who possessed these qualities: (S, L:) or, specially,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity, of ancestors:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"personal glory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility with goodness of actions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity, of actions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity; liberality;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karamN","text_ar":"كَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saxaA='N","text_ar":"سَخَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manly virtue"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moral goodness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruwo'apN","text_ar":"مُرُوْءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) [Accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used, and consequently each of the words in this art. derived from it, is tropical: but if so, it is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haqiyqap Eurofiy~ap","text_ar":"حَقِيقَة عُرْفِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or word so much used in a particular tropical sense as to be, in this sense, conventionally regarded as proper.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","L","S","K","M"]}]}}